<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Workflow 1: Competitive analysis</h2><p class="body">Prompt: 'Research [Competitor]. Their positioning, pricing if public, target customer, recent product launches, hiring patterns, customer reviews. Output: 1-page brief with key strategic implications for [your company].' Time: 30 minutes vs 8-12 hours unassisted.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Workflow 2: ICP refinement from win/loss data</h2><p class="body">Paste in closed-won and closed-lost deal data (anonymized if needed) with: 'Analyze these deals. What patterns distinguish wins from losses? What ICP characteristics correlate with wins? What disqualifiers correlate with losses? Output: refined ICP doc with evidence cited.'</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Workflow 3: Market sizing</h2><p class="body">'I'm building a market size analysis for [category]. Help me structure: TAM, SAM, SOM. Identify proxy data sources I can use. Surface comparable categories I should reference. Identify assumptions I need to validate.' Claude won't have proprietary data; will help you structure rigorously.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Workflow 4: Trend synthesis</h2><p class="body">Use Perplexity Pro for fresh sources → paste into Claude for synthesis: 'Synthesize the most important trends in [category] over the past 6 months. Distinguish noise from signal. Identify implications for [your company].' Pattern-recognition at superhuman speed.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Workflow 5: Customer interview synthesis</h2><p class="body">Conducted 10 customer interviews? Paste transcripts: 'Synthesize the themes across these 10 interviews. What pain points came up most? What solutions did they describe trying? What unspoken needs are implied? Quote verbatim where memorable.'</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Tools to pair with Claude</h2><p class="body">• Perplexity Pro ($20/mo) — for fresh-source research<br>• Notion or Google Docs — for storing and organizing research outputs<br>• Loom or Fathom — for interview recording + transcript<br><br>Total cost: ~$40/mo for individual researcher. Replaces $5K-$30K of analyst time per quarter.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What Claude can't do for market research</h2><p class="body">Three things:<br>1. <strong>Primary research.</strong> Surveys, interviews — humans do, Claude synthesizes.<br>2. <strong>Proprietary data analysis.</strong> Bring the data; Claude analyzes.<br>3. <strong>Real-time data.</strong> Claude's knowledge has a cutoff; pair with Perplexity for fresh.</p></div></section>



